Example Requests
These examples use the documented app route family. Add your bearer token header on protected endpoints.

Sign In
POST /app/auth/signin
{
    "username": "255700000001",
    "password": "secret123"
}
Read Session User
GET /app/get/getdata/session_user
No request body required
Update Profile And Password
POST /app/post/postdata/settings/profile/update
{
    "username": "John Doe",
    "phone": "0712345678",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "country": "Tanzania",
    "region": "Dar es Salaam",
    "new_password": "newpass123",
    "confirm_password": "newpass123"
}
Update Category Name
POST /app/post/postdata/stock/category/update
{
    "category_id": "CAT1001",
    "category": "Beverages"
}
Change Password Only
POST /app/post/postdata/home/password/change
{
    "new_password": "secure456",
    "confirm_password": "secure456"
}
Single Sale Record
GET /app/get/getdata/sales/record?sale_id=SALE1001
No request body required
Legacy JSON Endpoints
These older endpoints are still available for compatibility. Prefer the app auth/get/post routes for new integrations.

Method	Path	Description
GET	/api/v1/json/getdata/{endpoint}	Legacy JSON alias for helper-backed data reads and report-prefixed requests.
GET	/api/v1/json/getreport/{endpoint}	Legacy JSON alias for report endpoints.
GET	/api/v1/docs	HTML API documentation page protected by the daily PIN.
